896455_Speed indicates how many times longer the recording time is compared to the video length. It is related to the shooting interval. For example, when the speed is 15x, you will get 1 second of video for every 15 seconds you record. Videos are shot in 30 fps, which means 30 frames in 1 second of video. Therefore, at 15x, you have a shooting interval of 0.5 seconds.
